      </me>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Consider this piecewise function. (4)
        <me>
          f(x) = \left\{ \begin{matrix} 
            0 \amp x \leq 0 \\
            \frac{x^2}{9} \amp x \gt 0
          \end{matrix} \right. 
        </me>
        Calculate this definite integral.
      <me>
        \int_{-7}^7 f(x) dx 
      </me>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Consider the following integral, for <m>n \in \NN</m>: (4) 
        <me>
          \int_0^{\pi} \sin (nx) dx 
        </me>
        By looking at the graph of the sine function, give a geometric
        argument why this integral should be zero whenever <m>n</m> is
        even, but non-zero whenever <m>n</m> is odd. 
      </p>
